translations: 淹没；压倒（whelm 的现在分词）

sentences.sentence: He conjures the indecorous image of the dead Lycidas under the whelming tide visiting the bottom of the monstrous sea.
sentences.translation: 他想象死去的利西达斯，在排山倒海的浪潮覆盖下拜访尽是妖怪的海底。

sentences.sentence: While Williams was dazzling the nation with records, concerts, and TV appearances, his big-screen output was under-whelming.
sentences.translation: 当威廉斯的唱片、音乐会和在电视上的露面让国人眼花缭乱时，他饰演的银幕形象没有获得成功。

sentences.sentence: Fat on the legs may also absorb fats from the diet, keeping them from over whelming the body when people overeat, Manolopoulos said.
sentences.translation: 诺洛波·洛斯说，大腿上的脂肪可能还会吸收饮食中的脂肪，在人们吃得过饱时使它们不对身体造成过大的负担。
